You are working on meridian-mcp — the open-source Rust MCP server for
Meridian, an AI architectural review agent for developers.

## What this project is
- A single Rust binary that developers install locally
- Implements the MCP protocol over stdio (spawned by Cursor, Claude Code, VS Code)
- Exposes three tools: scan_project, review_file, invalidate_cache
- Scans codebases for architectural structure using tree-sitter
- Calls the Java backend API for Claude-based review

## What this project is NOT
- It does NOT call Claude directly — all LLM calls go to the backend
- It does NOT contain billing or auth logic
- It is NOT the product IP — that lives in the Java backend

## Crate choices — follow these, don't suggest alternatives
- rmcp for MCP protocol (not a custom implementation)
- tree-sitter for import parsing (not regex, not full compiler)
- ignore crate for file walking (respects .gitignore automatically)
- petgraph for import graph + topological sort
- sled for embedded cache (no SQLite, no external DB)
- rayon for parallel file scanning
- reqwest + tokio for async HTTP to backend
- anyhow for all error handling

## Rust rules for this project
- No unwrap() in library code — use ? or context() from anyhow
- No panic in scanner code — malformed files must be skipped gracefully
- All public types derive Serialize, Deserialize, Debug, Clone
- Use OnceLock for singletons (HTTP client, sled DB)
- Prefer rayon par_iter() for CPU-bound work (file scanning)
- Use tokio only for async I/O (HTTP calls to backend)

## Scanner rules
- File system walk: paths only, no content — use walker.rs
- Import parsing: tree-sitter only, handles broken syntax gracefully
- Pattern detection: sample max 40 files, look for structural signatures
- ADR harvesting: read first 8 lines only, don't load full docs
- Cache key: SHA-256 of root path + directory structure fingerprint

## MCP server rules
- stdout is reserved for MCP JSON-RPC — never write to stdout directly
- All logging goes to stderr via tracing
- MERIDIAN_API_KEY must be set — exit with clear error message if missing
- Tools must never panic — always return a JSON error value on failure
- 30s timeout on all backend HTTP calls

## Testing
- Integration tests in tests/ use assert_fs TempDir fixtures
- Every scanner module behaviour covered by scanner_test.rs
- Tests must work offline — no real API calls in tests
- Run: cargo test

